mingw-std-threads
*****************
   Decemvirate uses and includes the header-only mingw-std-threads library
   (<https://github.com/meganz/mingw-std-threads/>) as an alternative to
   libwinpthread for C++11 std::thread in MinGW builds. mingw-std-threads
   is licensed under the terms of the 2-clause BSD license. For the full
   text, see external/mingw-std-threads/LICENSE or
   <https://github.com/meganz/mingw-std-threads/blob/master/LICENSE>.

fmt
***
   Decemvirate includes fmt (<http://fmtlib.net/latest/>), licensed under
   the terms of the MIT license. For the full license text, see
   external/fmt/LICENSE.rst or
   <https://github.com/fmtlib/fmt/blob/master/LICENSE.rst>.

UTF-8 CPP
*********
   Decemvirate uses the lightweight header-only UTF-8 CPP library
   (<http://utfcpp.sourceforge.net/>) for handling UTF-8 encoded strings.
   UTF-8 CPP is licensed under the Boost Software License. See
   external/utf8cpp/utf8.hpp for details.

cxxopts
*******
   Decemvirate includes cxxopts (<https://github.com/jarro2783/cxxopts/>),
   licensed under the terms of MIT license. For the full license text,
   see external/cxxopts/LICENSE or
   <https://github.com/jarro2783/cxxopts/blob/master/LICENSE>.

xoreos and ScummVM code
***********************
   Decemvirate uses some code from the xoreos (<https://xoreos.org/>) project, a
   lot of which is based on ScummVM (<http://scummvm.org/>) code. xoreos is
   licensed under version 3 or later of the GNU General Public License and
   ScummVM is licensed under version 2 or later of the GNU General Public
   License. For the full license texts, see LICENSE.GPLv3 and LICENSE.GPLv2
   in the dist directory or <https://gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.html> and
   <https://gnu.org/licenses/gpl-2.0.html>.

Google Test
***********
   Decemvirate uses Google Test (<https://github.com/google/googletest>),
   Google's C++ test framework. Google Test is licensed under the terms of the
   3-clause BSD license. For the full license text, see tests/googletest/LICENSE
   or <https://github.com/google/googletest/blob/master/googletest/LICENSE>.
